reviews.review: As a standalone movie, this was the movie I had hoped episode 7 would be.  Somewhat chaotic, covering a lot of 30yr backstory shortly but providing a clear arcs for our new characters to grow.  As part of the whole Skywalker Universe: It is sad that 3 movies worth of arc was shoved into a single movie but I think that lies at the feet of JJ Abrams.  Going back and watching Episode VIII after time had passed, it became clearer that the goal of VIII was to strip the mythos/legends of the Jedi from their true purpose as they pertain to the Force. This paves the way for Ben and Rey to demonstrate what a true Jedi's role is.  Since the message was somewhat lost in translation between VIII & IX, IX suffered from having to clarify Luke's life lessons.  All in all, a solid ending assuming Disney doesn't get so greedy that they try and resurrect the bloodline from Ben and Rey's last scene.
Great close to the saga. JJ did an amazing job.
Break neck speed and action all the way through. Enjoyable for the casual fan but has cringe moments. Could have been so much better if it didnâ€™t need to retcon TLJ.

The movie had great battle scenes, a crazy twist, and lights  sabers. Overall the movie was great. It was more upsetting that we know these types of Star Wars movie's can be made yet the the first two in this new trilogy fell flat.

The beginning was terrible but what else could he do to get the story back on track.  Once you get past that it was good.  I thought how the delt with Princess Leah worked well and also Kylo.  Although they over did the life saving force/death stuff to much.  Both could survive at the end with out impact to story.

It is very fun to watch, but it is very clear from the start that this isn't by any means a "great conclusion of the Skywalker Saga". Hell, it doesn't even conclude the sequel trilogy very good. It so blatantly retcons episode 8 (which I did not love either btw) and tries to do too much in one movie, which in the end means that even some great moments don't get enough time to engage me.
It was fun and made me feel just as I did when I was a kid watching Star Wars. Don't think too hard about it, just enjoy
Finally the made a movie for the fans without caring for critics. Love it. Especially because critics are fuming

The beginning was paced a little weird but once the movie gained its footing, it was a fun, enjoyable ride. The story arch between Ben and Rey is incredible. Great end to the saga!
